Patch Set 9:

I'm curious if any other reviewers have thoughts about just always sending {} as the context?

I'm worried about the future cases where we will not have a context available to send with notifications, for example in the asynchronous tasks processing. The damage would be if someone is writing scripts downstream of the notifications and starts to depend on http stuff being available in the context--it sounds kind of like tight coupling to me.
